article.headline: Duquesne 91, Robert Morris 70
article.story: PITTSBURGH (AP) -- Ron Dokes broke a season-long slump scoring a season-high 26 points and grabbing 12 rebounds as Duquesne snapped a four game losing streak with a 91-70 win over Robert Morris on Sunday afternoon. Duquesne (3-6) upped their series record against Robert Morris (3-5) to 11-3. Duquesne trailed the Colonials 27-26 at the 7:23 mark in the first half, but led at halftime 45-37. Robert Morris could get no closer than five points at 62-57 as the Dukes pulled away for the victory. Duquesne forced Robert Morris into 17 turnovers while the Dukes had a season-low six turnovers. The Dukes held a 42-35 rebounding edge and had 16 offensive boards. Duquesne was 20 for 28 from the foul line and Robert Morris was 13 for 22 at the line. Elijah Palmer had 17 points for Duquesne. Jack Higgins contributed a career-high 12 points and Martin Osimani added a career-high 10 points for the Dukes. Aaron Thomas led Robert Morris with 23 points, Chaz McCromman had 16 points and Maurice Carter had 10 points.
